    "reason": "The data contract, validators, adapters, BM25 FlashRAG path, live DeepSeek answer/Judge evaluation, Fresh-Hard comparison, and human calibration audit are implemented and verified. Phase 7B raises the current best validated dataset to 100 chunks and 150 questions with Fresh-Hard retrieval evidence. Phase 7C adds a bounded real DeepSeek answer/Judge subset on the medium-plus Fresh-Hard split. Phase 7D adds a real OpenAlex-backed 124-paper candidate pool across 8 subtopics. Phase 7E converts those candidates into a machine pre-screening and full-text processing queue. Phase 7F adds provisional source decisions and a 115-row provisional source whitelist. Phase 7G refreshes OpenAlex metadata for all 115 provisional rows and probes real full-text access for the first 25 rows. Phase 7H expands full-text access/processability probing to all 115 provisional whitelist rows and builds a combined machine-assisted source verification matrix. The main hard gap remains final RAG.md demo scale: human source finalization, chunk extraction, and 300-500 question generation are still partial; dense/rerank methods have isolated readiness evidence but have not yet been executed."
  },
